## Best Practices

### 1. Start from Example

Copy an existing case similar to your scenario:
```bash
cp rtphelper/correlation_cases/inbound_xcc.yaml \
   rtphelper/correlation_cases/custom_case.yaml
```

### 2. Test in Isolation

Set high priority (90+) during development:
```yaml
priority: 95  # Will be tested first
enabled: true
```

### 3. Use Descriptive Names

‚ùå Bad:
```yaml
name: case1
description: "Custom case"
```

‚úÖ Good:
```yaml
name: inbound_carrier_xyz_with_ice
description: "Inbound calls from Carrier XYZ with ICE candidates in SDP"
```

### 4. Document Assumptions

```yaml
correlation:
  notes: |
    Assumptions:
    - Carrier always sends first INVITE
    - XCC header always present on INVITE #2
    - Early media negotiation uses 183 responses
    
    Known issues:
    - Does not handle re-INVITEs with codec changes
    - Fails if Call-ID changes mid-call
```

### 5. Use Annotations for Organization

```yaml
correlation:
  annotations:
    - "production"           # Deployment stage
    - "carrier:twilio"       # Carrier name
    - "topology:rtp_engine"  # Topology type
    - "region:us-west"       # Geographic region
```

### 6. Keep Tests Disabled in Production

```yaml
# Test cases:
priority: 90-100
enabled: false  # Disable in production

# Production cases:
priority: 10-80
enabled: true
```

### 7. Validate YAML Syntax

```bash
# Before committing:
python3 -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('rtphelper/correlation_cases/your_case.yaml'))"
```

