## Quick Reference Card

```yaml
# Minimal case template
name: <unique_name>
description: "<what_this_matches>"
priority: <0-100>  # Higher = evaluated first
enabled: <true|false>

detection:
  direction: <inbound|outbound|both>
  method: <INVITE|...>  # Optional
  headers:  # Optional
    - pattern: "<header_prefix>"
      case_insensitive: true
      required: false

correlation:
  strategy: <configurable|generic>
  config:  # For "configurable" strategy
    carrier_ip_source: "first_invite.src_ip"
    core_ip_source: "last_invite.dst_ip"
    response_priority: [200, 183]
    rtp_engine_detection: <enabled|disabled>

filters:
  template_set: <rtp_engine_topology|direct_topology|null>
  use_default_templates: true
```

**Common Priority Ranges**:
- 80-89: Multi Call-ID, high-specificity
- 70-79: RTP Engine with XCC
- 60-69: Direct media (no RTP Engine)
- 50-59: PSTN carriers
- 10-20: Generic fallbacks
- 0: Unknown (last resort)

**Template Sets**:
- `rtp_engine_topology`: 4 filters (3-hop: carrier ‚Üî RTP Engine ‚Üî core)
- `direct_topology`: 2 filters (2-hop: carrier ‚Üî core)

**IP Source Expressions**:
- `first_invite.src_ip` - Source IP of first INVITE
- `first_invite.dst_ip` - Destination IP of first INVITE
- `last_invite.src_ip` - Source IP of last INVITE
- `last_invite.dst_ip` - Destination IP of last INVITE
- `invite_with_changed_sdp.src_ip` - IP of INVITE that changed SDP (RTP Engine)

